MORNING REPORT: RADIO 
Desert Is Alive With Sound of Music : U.S. radio stations have received pledges 
of $30,000 and are seeking more donations to buy radios and batteries for use 
by American troops in the Persian Gulf, the National Assn. of Broadcasters said 
Thursday. The first shipment of radios already has arrived in the gulf and 
another 6,000 batteries and receivers will be en route next week, NAB said. 
CLAUDIA PUIG 
